==English==

===Set phrase===
'''[[unable]] [[to]] X one's [[way]] [[out]] [[of]] a [[paper]] [[bag]]'''

#(''formulaic'') {{idiom}} Unable to perform X with even a basic level of [[competence]] or [[effectiveness]].
#:''If he wants to be a writer someday, he needs to start practicing, because he '''couldn't write his way out of a paper bag''' right now.''

===Usage note===
*This is a formulaic phrase.  X may be replaced with nearly any verb. Variously stated as a "wet paper bag."